article.description: James Madison fends off Drexel 82-78, late rally falls short
article.headline: James Madison fends off Drexel 82-78, late rally falls short
article.linkText: James Madison fends off Drexel 82-78, late rally falls short
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Ron Curry scored 25 points and Yohanny Dalembert grabbed a clutch rebound in the final seconds as James Madison held off a late rally to defeat Drexel 82-78 on Wednesday, winning its fourth straight. The win completed a season sweep of Drexel by James Madison (17-11, 10-5 Colonial Athletic Association). Curry hit 5 of 9 shots and 13 of 16 at the foul line for his fourth game at 25 points or better in the Dukes' last eight. The Dragons (10-16, 8-7) closed with a quartet of 3-pointers -- two by Freddie Wilson -- in the final 1:44 to pull within 81-78 with 23 seconds remaining. Drexel hit 14 3s. Curry was fouled and made the front end of a one-and-one but Sammy Mojica missed two 3-pointers and Dalembert collared the final rebound. Tom Vodanovich scored a career-high 18 for the Dukes. Damion Lee scored 26 for Drexel, Wilson added 16.
